-- Tropical Storm Leslie to Become Hurricane Later Today
-- B y   R u p e r t   R o w l i n g
-- 2012-08-31T09:44:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-31/tropical-storm-leslie-to-become-hurricane-later-today-correct-.html
(Corrects number of named system in first paragraph)  Tropical Storm Leslie, the 12th
named system of the Atlantic season this year, is forecast to
become a hurricane later today, according to the National
Hurricane Center.  Leslie is located 940 miles (1510 kilometers) east of the
Leeward Islands in the Caribbean with maximum sustained winds of
65 miles per hour, the Miami-based center said in a 5 a.m.
advisory posted on its website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rupert Rowling in London at 
 rrowling@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
